# Styling Guidelines

## CSS Modules

- Use CSS modules for component styles: `*.module.css`
- Import modules: `import styles from "../styles/modules/header.module.css"`
- Use camelCase class names in CSS modules
- Apply classes: `class="${styles.navLink}"`
- Combine classes: `${styles.navLink} ${styles.active}`

## Global Styles

- Global styles in [src/style.css](mdc:apps/web/src/style.css) and [src/styles/index.css](mdc:apps/web/src/styles/index.css)
- Page-specific styles in `pages/{page}/index.css`
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Follow BEM-like naming for global classes

## CSS Module Location

CSS modules are in [src/styles/modules/](mdc:apps/web/src/styles/modules/):
- `assetCard.module.css`
- `authModal.module.css`
- `header.module.css`
- `map.module.css`
- etc.

## Styling Patterns

- Use CSS modules for scoped component styles
- Use global CSS for layout and base styles
- Use inline styles sparingly (only for dynamic values)
- Prefer CSS classes over inline styles
- Use CSS Grid/Flexbox for layouts

## Thai Language Support

- Ensure fonts support Thai characters
- Use appropriate line-height for Thai text
- Consider RTL if needed (though Thai is LTR)

## Responsive Design

- Use mobile-first approach
- Use media queries for breakpoints
- Test on various screen sizes
- Consider touch targets for mobile
